  "event_preview": "Pocono Raceway is a 2.5-mile (4.023 km) tri-oval in Blakeslee, Pennsylvania, known as the Tricky Triangle for its three unique turns with different radii and banking.\n\nThe MillerTech Battery 250 presented by KOA is the 17th race of the 2026 NASCAR O'Reilly Auto Parts Series season. It will be contested over 100 laps (250 miles) on Saturday, June 13 at 4 p.m. ET, with stages of 25/25/50 laps. This is the series' return to Pocono since 2025.\n\nJustin Allgaier arrives with momentum after winning at Nashville and will drive the No. 7 JR Motorsports Chevrolet. The 38-car field includes three Cup Series regulars — Cole Custer (No. 0), Connor Zilisch (No. 1), and William Byron (No. 88) — plus strong entries from Joe Gibbs Racing (Brandon Jones, Taylor Gray, William Sawalich, Brent Crews), Haas Factory Team (Sheldon Creed), and Richard Childress Racing (Jesse Love, Austin Hill).\n\nQualifying is crucial at Pocono: the winner has started inside the top 10 in eight of the last ten Xfinity races here. The all-time race lap record is 53.455 seconds (Christopher Bell, 2019), while Chase Elliott set the most recent qualifying mark in 2025 at 54.209 seconds / 166.024 mph. Track position and strategy will be key on the demanding Tricky Triangle.",
  "event_preview_ru": "Pocono Raceway — три-овал длиной 2,5 мили (4,023 км) в Blakeslee, Pennsylvania, известный как Tricky Triangle за три уникальных поворота с разным радиусом и уклоном.\n\nMillerTech Battery 250 presented by KOA — 17-й этап сезона NASCAR O'Reilly Auto Parts Series 2026. Гонка пройдёт на 100 кругов (250 миль) в субботу, 13 июня, в 4 p.m. ET, со стейджами 25/25/50 кругов. Серия возвращается на Pocono после 2025 года.\n\nJustin Allgaier приезжает с импульсом после победы в Nashville и выступит на No. 7 JR Motorsports Chevrolet. В составе 38 машин три постоянных гонщика Cup Series — Cole Custer (No. 0), Connor Zilisch (No. 1) и William Byron (No. 88) — плюс сильные заявки Joe Gibbs Racing (Brandon Jones, Taylor Gray, William Sawalich, Brent Crews), Haas Factory Team (Sheldon Creed) и Richard Childress Racing (Jesse Love, Austin Hill).\n\nКвалификация критична на Pocono: победитель стартовал в топ-10 в восьми из последних десяти гонок Xfinity здесь. Абсолютный рекорд круга гонки — 53,455 секунды (Christopher Bell, 2019), Chase Elliott установил последний квалификационный ориентир в 2025 — 54,209 секунды / 166,024 mph. Позиция на трассе и стратегия будут ключом на требовательном Tricky Triangle.",
